"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"*Whether you are a Figma expert, an artist or just curious this article will detail how to simply create an NFT from the Figma application.* \\n\\n### 1st - Get an Ethereum address\\n\\nIf you don’t have one you will need to create a wallet, the simplest way to do so is to create a wallet via Metamask. You will find [here](https://myterablock.medium.com/how-to-create-or-import-a-metamask-wallet-a551fc2f5a6b) a tutorial on how to create your first wallet.\\n\\n \\n **Reminder:**\\n\\n* Write down your seed phrase on paper or on a device that’s never connected and don’t lose it!\\n* Never, never share your private key.\\n\\n### 2nd - Download the NFTIZ Figma plugin\\n\\nYou need to download the [NFTIZ plugin](https://www.figma.com/community/plugin/1047579004421824566/NFTIZ) on Figma community. \\n\\n### 3rd - Mint your first NFT\\n\\nSo once you’re on Figma design you can create whatever you want. To process the mint you need to select a Frame and open the plugin as below. \\n \\n\\n![Select a Frame and open the plugin.](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/LifjJ1KjsqPl08-MdVO2q.png?height=598&width=1161)\\n\\nNow you need to fill in a name, a description, and the Ethereum address where you want to receive your NFT. Once it’s done you can click on mint.\\n\\n \\n What’s happening when you’re minting?\\n\\n* First, your Frame will be stored as a PNG on IPFS (Interplanetary File system).\\n* Then the metadata (name, description, image IPFS URL) of your NFT will be uploaded on IPFS too.\\n* Finally, your NFT will be minted on Polygon.\\n\\n![NFT minted ✅](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/WqxytGSnFCTI7xIg-GH6L.png?height=602&width=1162)\\n\\nNow, you can check your image stored on IPFS, your transaction on Polygonscan, and see your NFT on Opensea (note that Opensea can be slow to upload the data, it can take between 5 to 10 minutes). \\n \\n\\n### Do I need to pay gas fees?\\n\\nNo, as the process is using [“lazy minting”](https://nftschool.dev/tutorial/lazy-minting/) your transaction will be gasless.  So you don’t need to fill your wallet with MATIC or ETH to mint your first NFT. Keep in mind that if you want to sell your NFT on Opensea you will need to sign a transaction that will cost gas.\\n\\nEt voilà.\\n\\n![Now you can sell your NFT on Opensea.](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/3zTAnP6PLnY_LvMaYZJ5x.png?height=760&width=1439)\\n\\n*NFTIZ, is free and open-source, you can go on our [website](https://nftiz-app.xyz/) or send us a dm on Twitter if you want to improve the tool. Also if you love the tool and you want to contribute, you can tip us :).*\",\"timestamp\":1639230962,\"title\":\"How to turn your Figma creation into an NFT?\"},\"digest\":\"girNZeb3nvrL-gL4TXhNMOueHW5rCD9qyI241vehqEc\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xcB7eA0eC36670AA13088C4372fe8636D4D2b574f\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"RoaxkncQqXHNZFtAMk9iTzR6bh0B4j3-BULsep2f_Z4\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"ez2AsUWeNQfX78I5ZckQ44_1kC088OKKYK0rvGizmmM\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"DT3V6f3Ty52T_l60jHMED1h53Y7DzUG0i_dG4xjwDmGeb33pUgo__-rkIKm-ylDx_SQrwYTrPb9INZg6Cou_zg\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0xa00b8c5f6d25167c6d1ecf41a85eef0e0a229847b435036772bfff9193fb7ec63969794cba92d3303f189fa276153674c25589a625d6438c0ff50b8d09a185411c\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"RoaxkncQqXHNZFtAMk9iTzR6bh0B4j3-BULsep2f_Z4\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"ez2AsUWeNQfX78I5ZckQ44_1kC088OKKYK0rvGizmmM\\\"}\",\"algorithm\":{\"name\":\"ECDSA\",\"hash\":\"SHA-256\"}},\"nft\":{},\"version\":\"12-21-2020\",\"originalDigest\":\"E12TAg1z_Y7OckSGEjG6GvuYOGHQY00kM5jkNV-NJtk\"}"